Washington Street, west side, south from Cedar Street.

June 26, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

Washington Street, south from Cedar Street, as photographed across a clearance extending to Albany Street. Beyond same appears the dark bulk of P. S. No. 29. This occupies the west frontage between Albany and Carlisle Street's. Individually in each is a dominant structure. These are (left to right) the unfinished Irving Trust Co. Bldg., the newly completed 35 story building, No. 21 Rector Street, and the massive New York Post Bldg. at No. 75 West St. The six story tenements on the left, comprising No's. 133-9 Washington Street and No's. 7-11 Albany Street, forming the N. E. corner have been sold. Included also is No. 126 Cedar Street. This was reported in the New York Sun of August 25, 1938.

1 & 2 July 30, 1930
